fields.Title: WESTCOAST / GARY
fields.Description: Gary the Cryptofascist is a friend of Morell's. Also trying to find the cryptid. Wears armour stolen from the hanged man under his clothes. Has Man from Hjelmdall books etc.

fields.Title: You: ""I would -- but I don't know *how*.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I would -- but I don't know *how*."

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""Revachol used to be flaming rhino..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Revachol used to be flaming rhino once, a long time ago..." he says and then pauses, thoughtfully.

fields.Title: Morell, the Cryptozoologist: ""GARY! WHAT'S GOING ON?!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "GARY! WHAT'S GOING ON?!"

fields.Title: Lena, the Cryptozoologist's wife: ""Shame on you! Give the cuirass to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Shame on you! Give the cuirass to the officer at once!" The woman looks at you, her eyes soft and pleading.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It's okay." The lieutenant jots so..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's okay." The lieutenant jots something down in his notebook. "It was a loose end and you're tying it up now."

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: "The man simply nods, his long blond..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The man simply nods, his long blond hair falling on his shoulders.

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""Okay, but... I told you everything..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, but... I told you everything. What else can I say?"

fields.Title: Logic: "But how is this combustible fluid l..."
fields.Dialogue Text: But how is this combustible fluid lit?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant sighs without lookin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant sighs without looking up from his notes.

fields.Title: Jump to: [You: ""So you deliver things. What kinds..."]
Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""I'm doing all I can in this econom..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm doing all I can in this economy, officer."

fields.Title: You: ""The lieutenant is a native of Reva..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The lieutenant is a native of Revachol."
fields.Alternate1: "The lieutenant is a true Vacholiere. Why did you call him a Seolite?"

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: "He smiles broadly."
fields.Dialogue Text: He smiles broadly.

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""You heard me. I deliver topping pi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You heard me. I deliver topping pies. It's temporary. I'm looking for another job. Not many jobs for good men out there these days."

fields.Title: You: ""I don't buy this theory.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't buy this theory."

fields.Title: You: ""I think I broke into your apartmen..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I think I broke into your apartment. I'm very sorry."

fields.Title: You: ""I saw the poster in your apartment..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I saw the poster in your apartment. You know, I'm a Hjelmdallermann fan myself."

fields.Title: Composure: "As he lowers his tone he hunches hi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: As he lowers his tone he hunches his back.

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""Of course, of course." He forces a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Of course, of course." He forces a grin, no doubt hiding some *colossal* anal beads up his butt as he does so.

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""I knew you'd figure it out, office..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I knew you'd figure it out, officer." He sighs heavily. "I'm sorry I didn't tell you at once. I was..." He unbuttons the shirt.

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""Meatless bacon, avocado, glazed fi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Meatless bacon, avocado, glazed figs, basil, and tiny chunks of pineapple, seasoned with lime zest, freshly ground pepper -- and just a pinch of paprika for the officer!"

fields.Title: Logic: "Yellow Man? Might this be the owner..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yellow Man? Might this be the owner of that mug you found in the trash? This is something to ask him about, after a little probing first...

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""Hello again! How do you do, office..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hello again! How do you do, officer? I'm *still* waiting for Mr. F-ing Field Research over there to be done with his traps."

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""Dark times will do that to good me..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Dark times will do that to good men." He nods gravely, then shifts his gaze to the floor tiles.

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""I like nature, just not this blood..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I like nature, just not this bloody coast. It's mostly drunks and degenerates that come here."

fields.Title: You: ""Do you know anything about the man..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Do you know anything about the man hanged behind the Whirling-in-Rags?"

fields.Title: You: ""I don't know. I liked the previous..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't know. I liked the previous racists better."

fields.Title: You: ""Honestly, I feel bad about it. The..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Honestly, I feel bad about it. The article you wanted to write -- don't let this dissuade you from writing it."

fields.Title: You: ""Try not to shit yourself Gary. It'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Try not to shit yourself Gary. It's just an open door."

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""Of course. Of course." He looks ar..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Of course. Of course." He looks around nervously. "I won't do it again. If there's anything I can do to assist you -- or the Union -- just ask, okay? I'll try to help if I can."

fields.Title: Drama: "We're not detecting falsehoods, sir..."
fields.Dialogue Text: We're not detecting falsehoods, sire. He's gearing up to admit the truth.

fields.Title: Lena, the Cryptozoologist's wife: ""Gary didn't mean to interfere with..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Gary didn't mean to interfere with your investigation, officers, he's just... thick headed and poor as dirt. But he's always helped us, given us a place to stay. And he's followed Morell into god knows what jungles..."

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""I always thought it was the Union,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I always thought it was the Union, but... I sure as hell won't go around saying that anymore. You have my word. I don't know -- and I won't be running my mouth on this subject anymore."

fields.Title: Endurance: "I'm satisfied. Are you satisfied? B..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I'm satisfied. Are you satisfied? Because I am.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Using a standard form, officer." T..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Using a standard form, officer." The lieutenant pulls out a sheet of carbon copy paper, scribbles something on it, then tears out the bottom page and hands it to Gary.

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""I'm sorry, okay? I thought I could..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm sorry, okay? I thought I could cut costs. I shouldn't have. I shouldn't have disgraced myself."

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""Of course. Of course.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Of course. Of course."

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Sounds like some conspiracy topic...."
fields.Dialogue Text: Sounds like some conspiracy topic. You might be able to discuss it with him when the lieutenant isn't here. *If* you can remember it.

fields.Title: You: ""Do you deliver drugs?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Do you deliver drugs?"

fields.Title: Logic: "It makes sense that a technological..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It makes sense that a technologically advanced nation that produces a lot of *microtechnology* would have foreign governments as customers. That in itself doesn't prove anything.

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: "He leans in so close you can feel h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He leans in so close you can feel his lukewarm breath against your jaw. "Just do your part as an officer of the RCM."

fields.Title: You: ""Mr. Claire must be very angry with..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Mr. Claire must be very angry with you."

fields.Title: You: ""I am..." (Rip out a fine slip.) "F..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I am..." (Rip out a fine slip.) "For 20 reál."

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""I told you everything -- I just to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I told you everything -- I just took the cuirass that's all. I promise. I don't know anything else."

fields.Title: You: "Let it go."
fields.Dialogue Text: Let it go.

fields.Title: You: ""Yes! Our *lucky* racist.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes! Our *lucky* racist."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""The weather vane has turned," the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The weather vane has turned," the lieutenant remarks with a smirk. "He cannot be un-turned."

fields.Title: Lena, the Cryptozoologist's wife: ""He's a scaredy cat." The woman loo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He's a scaredy cat." The woman looks at Gary, her eyes motherly.

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""Most of the Seolites may be shifty..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Most of the Seolites may be shifty, but the ones in Revachol have always been loyal to Revachol -- and the Suzerain too. I..." He trails off.

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""Then I came out to clean up the ra..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Then I came out to clean up the rags because *no one else would*. I put them into the Whirling's trash -- along with a broken mug, admittedly..." He changes his mind mid-sentence.

fields.Title: You: ""Gary, do you know how to turn back..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Gary, do you know how to turn back time?"

fields.Title: Endurance: "But still... he's definitely one of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: But still... he's definitely one of us. Longs for the Old Days - the *Old Ways*. He's likely to know how to turn back time. Ask him!

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""I mean…" He turns toward Kim. "Off..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I mean…" He turns toward Kim. "Officers."

fields.Title: You: ""That's not an answer.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's not an answer."

fields.Title: You: ""Thank you, sir. It's not often tha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Thank you, sir. It's not often that the RCM receives the recognition that it deserves."

fields.Title: You: ""Do you deliver guns?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Do you deliver guns?"

fields.Title: You: ""What?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What?"

fields.Title: You: ""I think I see where you're going w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I think I see where you're going with this..."

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""And keep an eye on that partner of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "And keep an eye on that partner of yours." He lets the silence linger, then concludes: "Good talk."

fields.Title: You: ""I can *see* you recognize it. It's..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I can *see* you recognize it. It's in your eyes."

fields.Title: Drama: "He is trying to avoid lying to you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He is trying to avoid lying to you outright in case you really have been to his apartment.

fields.Title: You: ""Still seems suspicious. Did I ment..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Still seems suspicious. Did I mention the mug was found at the scene of a lynching?"
fields.Alternate1: "You're acting kind of suspicious. Did I mention the mug was found at the scene of a lynching?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Disgraced?" The lieutenant raises..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Disgraced?" The lieutenant raises his eyebrows and looks up. "No need for the histrionics, sir. It was, after all, just a trash container."

fields.Title: You: ""Yes, he insisted that I open the d..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, he insisted that I open the door to your apartment."

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: Morell, the Cryptozoologist: ""What did you do, Gary?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What did you do, Gary?"

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""Hey, man." He blushes. "All I mean..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hey, man." He blushes. "All I meant was there are not many Seolites around here. I'm just stating a fact."

fields.Title: You: ""Why did you lie to me, Gary?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Why did you lie to me, Gary?"

fields.Title: You: ""Do you know who killed the hanged..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Do you know who killed the hanged man?"

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "There *probably* is a follow-up to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There *probably* is a follow-up to this, but you can't think of any. Doesn't matter. Waste of time anyway. Gotta keep moving.

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""Okay, I deserve that -- and I won'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, I deserve that -- and I won't do it again." He accepts the slip of copy paper with a bow. "You have my word."

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""I was only cleaning up. I live rig..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I was only cleaning up. I live right across the yard from where he was hanged and I saw him stripped naked. All the clothes lying around in the yard, smelling... People are animals, you know..."

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""The flames are not just for decora..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The flames are not just for decoration. They are an integral part of the beast's mating behaviour."

fields.Title: You: ""How so?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "How so?"

fields.Title: You: ""You said you'd tell me about Seoli..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You said you'd tell me about Seolites, when Kim isn't here. He isn't here."

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""That's not what I was implying at..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's not what I was implying at all..." He eyes the lieutenant nervously. "But, of course, you're just kidding, officer."

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""Even as Seol remains closed off fr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Even as Seol remains closed off from the world, Seolite agents have been slowly advancing through the echelons of power on the other isolae."

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""They come as apparently well-meani..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "They come as apparently well-meaning immigrants. Sometimes students -- they learn our *violin* and *cello*. But more often tech workers in cybernetics and similar advanced industries."

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""Please, be careful!" He waves his..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Please, be careful!" He waves his hands energetically. "Don't let on that you know about the Seolite Conspiracy. Who knows what he might do to you..."

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""Officer, please..." He raises both..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Officer, please..." He raises both hands. "Let me explain. It's not like *that...*"

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""So I can use the Whirling's trash..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So I can use the Whirling's trash compactor to store my own stuff," he says, bowing shamefully like a fallen knight. "Garbage disposal is expensive as hell, the damn Himeans run it like a mob..."

fields.Title: Perception (Hearing): "Once more you hear that odd clickin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Once more you hear that odd clicking sound coming from Gary.

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""In my home, yes, when I was going..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "In my home, yes, when I was going to..." His face turns pale. "How did you *know?*"

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""How...?" The colour drains from hi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "How...?" The colour drains from his face.

fields.Title: You: ""Just doing Mr. Claire a small favo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Just doing Mr. Claire a small favour."

fields.Title: You: ""To explode the gender binary. You..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "To explode the gender binary. You should be more open about your views, though. Let those beads hang out."

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "What he means is: working on the ca..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What he means is: working on the case is taking a toll on *you*, and working with you is taking a toll on *him*.

fields.Title: You: ""Yummm. I can taste it already!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yummm. I can taste it already!"

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""Enjoy." He smiles broadly."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Enjoy." He smiles broadly.
fields.Alternate1: He smiles broadly. "Enjoy. It's the least I can do for an officer -- and a Union man too!"

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""I'm just waiting for my friend Mor..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm just waiting for my friend Morell to finish up with his insect traps so we can return to civilization."
fields.Alternate1: "I'm just waiting for my friend Morell to finish up with his insect traps," he quickly changes the subject, "so we can return to civilization."

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: "He turns toward Kim. "I mean... *of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He turns toward Kim. "I mean... *officers*."

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "Yellow Man! That sounds awfully fam..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yellow Man! That sounds awfully familiar. Something to ask about later?

fields.Title: You: ""Drunks and degenerates -- that's m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Drunks and degenerates -- that's my crew!"

fields.Title: You: ""Not a lover of the great outdoors?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Not a lover of the great outdoors?"

fields.Title: You: ""I can buy into that. A flaming rhi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I can buy into that. A flaming rhino."

fields.Title: You: ""Are you, Gary? Are you a racist?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Are you, Gary? Are you a racist?"

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "Return without the lieutenant -- fo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Return without the lieutenant -- for this? Your balance organ thinks it's a waste of time.

fields.Title: Composure: "Yes. Like a piece of ceramic armour..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes. Like a piece of ceramic armour, for example. One that makes a clicking sound when the plates meet each other, resembling pearls or marbles. Stolen from the corpse in the yard near where he lives.

fields.Title: Authority: "*Serious* question time. This man i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: *Serious* question time. This man is no innocent. No one is.

fields.Title: Authority: "See? He's being evasive. Shake him..."
fields.Dialogue Text: See? He's being evasive. Shake him up, show him who's boss.

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "He pronounces 'Revachol' with a har..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He pronounces 'Revachol' with a hard k, unlike other people.

fields.Title: Perception (Hearing): "The sound you heard was not the sou..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The sound you heard was not the sound of something easily abandoned.

fields.Title: You: ""All right.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "All right."

fields.Title: Composure: "He's not feeling too comfortable in..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He's not feeling too comfortable in his own skin. Odd, I'd say.

fields.Title: You: ""Okay. Then what happened?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay. Then what happened?"

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""Exactly! That's exactly what it wa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Exactly! That's exactly what it was -- civic duty."

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""Yellow Man!" He turns toward Kim...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yellow Man!" He turns toward Kim. "I mean... officer."

fields.Title: You: "Why's he shifting around like that?..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Why's he shifting around like that? Analyze Gary's composure.

fields.Title: You: ""I'm into cryptids. Do you have a f..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm into cryptids. Do you have a favourite?"

fields.Title: You: ""What do you do, then? If not crypt..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What do you do, then? If not cryptozoology?"

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Seol is indeed famous for its advan..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Seol is indeed famous for its advanced microtechnology, and for exporting it to foreign governments. Kijion Eendracht, the owner of Eendracht Airworks, is Seolite...

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""...and use their superior technolo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "...and use their superior technology to blackmail, mislead, and manipulate, turning high-ranking people in government and corporations into Seolite agents."

fields.Title: You: ""Is this your mug?" (Hold up the Ye..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Is this your mug?" (Hold up the Yellow Man Mug.)
fields.Alternate1: "Lets talk about the mug-trash situation again."

fields.Title: Empathy: "He's disappointed in you and sees n..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He's disappointed in you and sees no point of arguing further.

fields.Title: You: ""Alright, I believe you. You look l..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Alright, I believe you. You look like the kind of man who knows it's a *crime* to lie to an officer."

fields.Title: You: ""That clinking I just heard when yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That clinking I just heard when you moved."

fields.Title: You: ""Have you found your door open late..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Have you found your door open lately?"

fields.Title: You: ""No, I did. Took a look around, too.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, I did. Took a look around, too."

fields.Title: You: ""No, *I* did, per his request.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, *I* did, per his request."

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""But, officer…" He shakes his head..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "But, officer…" He shakes his head slowly. "I'm not wearing any women's clothes."

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""Good one. Yeah, good one officer."..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good one. Yeah, good one officer." He forces a grin. "You really have a courageous sense of humour."
fields.Alternate1: "Good one. Good one. Joking around again, officer." He forces a grin. "You really do have a courageous sense of humour."

fields.Title: Lena, the Cryptozoologist's wife: ""Gary, what's going on?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Gary, what's going on?"

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""Dark times will do that to good me..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Dark times will do that to good men." He nods gravely, then shifts his gaze to the pile of soggy logs at his feet.

fields.Title: You: ""I am." (Rip out a fine slip.) "For..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I am." (Rip out a fine slip.) "For 250 reál -- the maximum."

fields.Title: You: ""I am..." (Rip out a fine slip.) "F..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I am..." (Rip out a fine slip.) "For 100 reál."

fields.Title: Morell, the Cryptozoologist: ""WHAT DID YOU DO, GARY?!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "WHAT DID YOU DO, GARY?!"

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: "He looks around, half-ashamed, half..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He looks around, half-ashamed, half-relieved.

fields.Title: Drama: "An infant could see he's not tellin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: An infant could see he's not telling the truth -- but he's too scared to admit more wrongdoing.

fields.Title: Half Light: "Don't be so relieved yet, Gary. Thi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Don't be so relieved yet, Gary. This bad cop may have been in *your* apartment, admiring your mug collection. Perhaps a little intimidation?

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""Always a pleasure to see an office..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Always a pleasure to see an officer of the law!"

fields.Title: You: ""Come on, man. You're not under sus..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Come on, man. You're not under suspicion yet, but you will be if you keep evading questions."
fields.Alternate1: "C'mon, you've already behaved suspiciously with the trash container business, stop evading the question"

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""Sure. If you want, I could get you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sure. If you want, I could get you one for free if we ever meet in the city, officer. Wheat free. Just ask me later."

fields.Title: Shivers: "Every day, the wind shifts the reed..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Every day, the wind shifts the reeds and whatever was left in them: tambourines and condom wrappers, plastic and glass bottles, the smell of decay.

fields.Title: You: ""I had to. For Mr. Claire. I'm a ba..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I had to. For Mr. Claire. I'm a bad cop, I know, but I felt like I had to do it..."

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""But... why were you in my apartmen..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "But... why were you in my apartment, officer?"

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""Very generous of you to help us ou..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Very generous of you to help us out, officer. I'm sure glad to be back from that little excursion."

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""Hello again! Very generous of you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hello again! Very generous of you to help us out, officer. I can't wait to get out of here."

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Yellow Man? Feels significant someh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yellow Man? Feels significant somehow, him saying that. You should ask him about it, later...

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""Nothing! Nothing... just answering..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nothing! Nothing... just answering some questions. Helping out the law..."

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""I won't cause any more trouble," h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I won't cause any more trouble," he whispers. "I'll be Mr. Cooperation. The Union doesn't have to worry about me -- they're honest Vacholieres. Honest men."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Great." The lieutenant mumbles. "F..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Great." The lieutenant mumbles. "First the sandwich, now a pie..."

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""Because I was weak." He says, star..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Because I was weak." He says, staring at nothing in particular. "I should have told you the moment I saw you, but..."

fields.Title: Logic: "The *stupid* way?"
fields.Dialogue Text: The *stupid* way?

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""Whooh," he's visibly relieved. "Th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Whooh," he's visibly relieved. "Thank you, you won't regret this. I won't use another man's property to dump my garbage *ever* again."

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""All right. Of course, officer.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "All right. Of course, officer."

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""Hello! I'm Gary. How do you do, of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hello! I'm Gary. How do you do, officer?"

Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""Yeah, well -- Revachol used to be..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, well -- Revachol used to be flaming rhino once, a long time ago..." he says and then pauses, thoughtfully. "That seems unlikely too, doesn't it?"

fields.Title: You: ""It seems dangerous that immigrants..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It seems dangerous that immigrants would go into fields that affect information technology."

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""You're not going to fine me, are y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're not going to fine me, are you?"

fields.Title: You: ""How did you get into the trash con..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "How did you get into the trash container?"

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""What... sound?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What... sound?"

fields.Title: You: ""And you're a big Man from Hjelmdal..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "And you're a big Man from Hjelmdall fan?"

fields.Title: You: ""Mr. Evrart Claire thought it neces..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Mr. Evrart Claire thought it necessary to unlock your apartment."

fields.Title: Gary, the Cryptofascist: ""I don't pray, officer. Faith in no..."
